Function Reference/get lastpostdate « WordPress Codex
-----------

Retrieve the date the the last post was published.

The server timezone is the default and is the difference between
[GMT](/Glossary#GMT "Glossary") and server time. The '`blog`' value is
the date when the last post was posted. The '`gmt`' is when the last
post was posted in [GMT](/Glossary#GMT "Glossary") formatted date.

Usage
-----

` <?php get_lastpostdate( $timezone ) ?> `

Parameters
----------

 `$timezone` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) The location to get the time. Can be '`gmt`', '`blog`',
    or '`server`'.
    Default: 'server'

Return Values
-------------

 (string) 
:   The date of the last post.

Examples
--------

Notes
-----

-   Uses:
    [`apply_filters()`](/Function_Reference/apply_filters "Function Reference/apply filters")
    Calls '`get_lastpostdate`' filter
-   Uses global: (`mixed`) `$cache_lastpostdate` Stores the date the
    last post.
-   Uses global: (`object`)
    [`$wpdb`](/Class_Reference/wpdb "Class Reference/wpdb")
-   Uses global: (`integer`) `$blog_id` The Blog ID.

Change Log
----------

Since: 0.71

Source File
-----------

`get_lastpostdate()` is located in `wp-includes/post.php`.

